<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/jgback.jpg">

<CENTER>
<!--#include virtual="/Belarus/include_bsig_banner.txt"-->
<H1>All Belarus Database</H1>
</CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><FONT SIZE=+1>
<P>The "All Belarus Database" is a multiple-database search,
which incorporates all of the following databases, which 
contain over 100,000 entries from Belarus. </P>
</FONT></BLOCKQUOTE>

<table cellpadding=5>
<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/brest.htm">The Phoenix Project</a> <br>
<font size=2>Names and demographics of over 12,000 people 
in the Brest Ghetto; a database of Holocaust victims 
drawn from Soviet archives. </font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/grodno.htm">Grodno Gubernia 1912 Voters List</a> <br>
<font size=2>Names of over 26,000 men of Grodno Gubernia who were eligible 
to vote in the Russian parliamentary elections in 1912. </font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/rechitsa.htm">Rechitsa Uezd 1906 Voters List</a> <br>
<font size=2>Names of nearly 3,000 men of Rechitsa District (Minsk Gubernia) who 
were eligible to vote in the Russian Duma elections in 1906. </font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/minsk.htm">Minsk Surnames</a> <br>
<font size=2>Index of surnames appearing in the LDS microfilms of the
Jewish vital records of the city of Minsk.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/vsiabelarus.htm"><I>Vsia Rossiia</I> - 1903 &amp; 1911 
   Minsk Gubernia, 1911 Mogilev Gubernia, 1911 Vitebsk gubernia</a> <br>
<font size=2>Over 10,000 Jewish businesses, from 1903 and 1911 Russian business
directories.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<a href="/databases/mogilevb.htm">Mogilev Birth Index of boys, 1864-1894</a><BR>
<font size=2>Index of over 9,800 male births in Mogilev, 
listed by father's given name.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<A HREF="/databases/nowogrodskie.jri.htm">1929 Business Directory - 
Nowogrodek Province</A><BR>
<font size=2>Over 15,000 entries from a Polish business directory.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<A HREF="/databases/Belarus/MinskHomeowners.htm">Minsk City Homeowners Lists, 1889 and 1911</A><BR>
<font size=2>Nearly 9,000 homeowners from 1889 and 1911 Minsk guidebooks.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<A HREF="/databases/Belarus/PinskGhetto.htm">Pinsk Ghetto List, 1942</A><BR>
<font size=2>Data on over 18,000 Jews in the Pinsk ghetto in late 1941 or 1942.</font></td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td valign=top><img src="/images/jgtree2.gif" align=bottom></td>
<td valign=top>
<A HREF="/Belarus/intro_rev_list.htm">Revision Lists</A>
<img src="/images/new11.gif"><BR>
<font size=2>1,000 records from <I>Reviska Skazka</I>, 19th century Czarist 
tax censuses.</font></td>
</tr>

</table>

                                
<HR>

<FORM Method="POST" Action="/wconnect/wc.isa?jg~jgsys~belarus">
                                                                
<P>Enter <B>text</B> <INPUT name="srch" size=40> to search 
for in the <I>All Belarus Database</I>, <BR>
and choose the <B>type</B> of search  
<SELECT NAME="srch2">
<OPTION VALUE="SD">Surname -- Daitch-Mokotoff Soundex
<OPTION VALUE="SE">Surname -- Exact Spelling
<OPTION VALUE="TD">Town -- Daitch-Mokotoff Soundex
<OPTION VALUE="TE">Town -- Exact Spelling
<OPTION VALUE="GT">Global Text Search
</SELECT>
</P>

<P>For "Global Text Search" you can search for single words, or you
can search for word combinations using 'AND' and 'OR'. &nbsp;  
<NOBR>For example:</NOBR> <NOBR>"<I>TRAUB and Zelman</I>",</NOBR>
<NOBR>"<I>KAPLAN or SHAPIRO</I>".</NOBR></P>

<P><INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="Search the All Belarus Database"></P>
</FORM>

<HR>

<P> &nbsp; </P>

